                    <!-- ─── Project Overview ─── -->
                    <div class="case-study-section">
                        <h2 class="section-heading" id="project-overview">Project Overview</h2>
                        <p>In this project, I performed deep-dive data analysis on Google's public <strong>Google
                                Analytics Sessions dataset</strong>. The dataset contains obfuscated web analytics data
                            from the Google Merchandise Store, a real e-commerce website.</p>
                        <p>The primary objective of this project is to demonstrate advanced SQL capabilities in solving
                            complex e-commerce business problems. By examining millions of session logs and hits, I
                            explore various behavioral metrics. This page highlights two of the most critical deep-dive
                            case studies from that analysis: <strong>Conversion Funnel Analysis</strong> and
                            <strong>Purchaser vs. Non-Purchaser Behavior</strong>.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Case Study 1 Wrapper -->
                    <div class="case-study-section">
                        <h2 class="section-heading" id="case-study-1">Case Study 1: E-Commerce Conversion Funnel
                            Analysis</h2>

                        <!-- 1. The Business Challenge -->
                        <h3 class="sub-heading">The Business Challenge</h3>
                        <p>The product team knew traffic was healthy — but revenue wasn't growing proportionally.
                            The core question was: <strong>where exactly are users dropping off in the buying
                                journey?</strong> Without mapping the full funnel from product view to cart to purchase,
                            there was no clear signal on whether the bottleneck was product discovery, cart friction, or
                            checkout hesitation.</p>

                        <!-- 2. My Approach -->
                        <h3 class="sub-heading">My Approach</h3>
                        <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
                            <span class="badge bg-primary rounded-pill me-3 px-2 py-1">1</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Funnel Mapping via Action Types:</strong> Leveraged
                                <code>eCommerceAction.action_type</code> codes to classify each hit — <em>'2' = Product
                                    View</em>, <em>'3' = Add to Cart</em>, <em>'6' = Purchase</em>.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
                            <span class="badge bg-primary rounded-pill me-3 px-2 py-1">2</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Revenue Guard:</strong> Applied a <code>productRevenue IS NOT NULL</code> filter
                                on purchase events to ensure only genuine completed transactions were counted, excluding
                                abandoned checkouts.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
                            <span class="badge bg-primary rounded-pill me-3 px-2 py-1">3</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Rate Calculation:</strong> Computed Add-to-Cart Rate
                                (<code>num_addtocart / num_product_view</code>) and Purchase Rate
                                (<code>num_purchase / num_product_view</code>) as percentages to make the funnel loss
                                comparable across months.
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- 3. Solution (Code Snippet) -->
                        <h3 class="sub-heading">Solution</h3>
                        <p class="mb-3">The query uses a two-step CTE to first categorize hit events, then aggregate
                            the funnel counts and calculate conversion rates per month:</p>
                        <div class="code-snippet-container shadow-sm">
                            <div class="code-header">
                                <span><i class="bi bi-code-slash me-2"></i>SQL Query</span>
                                <span class="badge bg-light text-dark border">BigQuery (GA Sessions 2017)</span>
                            </div>
                            <div id="sql-container-cs1"
                                style="max-height: 200px; overflow: hidden; transition: max-height 0.5s ease; position: relative;">
                                <pre class="mb-0"><code>WITH
  data_overview AS(
  SELECT
    FORMAT_DATE('%Y%m',PARSE_DATE('%Y%m%d',date)) month,
    eCommerceAction.action_type action_type,
    totals.transactions,
    product.productRevenue
  FROM `bigquery-public-data.google_analytics_sample.ga_sessions_2017*`,
    UNNEST(hits) hits,
    UNNEST(product) product
  WHERE _table_suffix BETWEEN '0101' AND '0331'
  ),

  data_count AS(
  SELECT
    month,
    COUNTIF(action_type = '2') num_product_view,
    COUNTIF(action_type = '3') num_addtocart,
    COUNTIF(action_type = '6' AND productRevenue IS NOT NULL) num_purchase,
  FROM data_overview
  GROUP BY month
  ORDER BY month
  )

SELECT
  *,
  ROUND((num_addtocart/num_product_view * 100.0),2) add_to_cart_rate,
  ROUND((num_purchase/num_product_view * 100.0),2) purchase_rate
FROM data_count</code></pre>
