                        <!-- 4. Key Insights -->
                        <h3 class="sub-heading">Key Insights</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Improving Funnel Efficiency Over Time:</strong> The Add-to-Cart
                                Rate grew from <strong>28.47% in January to 37.29% in March</strong> — a 31% relative
                                improvement. This suggests either seasonal intent strengthening or product/UX changes
                                beginning to take effect.</li>
                            <li class="mb-2"><strong>The Cart-to-Purchase Gap Remains the Biggest Leak:</strong>
                                Despite healthy Add-to-Cart rates (~28–37%), the Purchase Rate sits at only
                                <strong>8–13%</strong>. This means roughly <strong>65–72% of users who add to cart
                                    never complete a purchase</strong> — a cart abandonment problem.
                            </li>
                            <li class="mb-2"><strong>March Outperforms:</strong> March shows the strongest conversion
                                across all metrics — highest Add-to-Cart Rate (37.29%), highest Purchase Rate (12.64%),
                                and highest absolute purchase volume (2,977). This could reflect a seasonal demand spike
                                or a successful promotional push.</li>
                        </ul>
                        </ul>

                    </div>
