                    <!-- Case Study 2 Wrapper -->
                    <div class="case-study-section">
                        <h2 class="section-heading" id="case-study-2">Case Study 2: Purchaser vs. Non-Purchaser
                            Behavior</h2>

                        <!-- 1. The Business Challenges -->
                        <h3 class="sub-heading">The Business Challenge</h3>
                        <p>Marketing was spending budget equally on all visitors, but not all visitors are equal.
                            The growth team needed to understand: <strong>what separates a buyer from a
                                browser?</strong> Specifically, do purchasers engage more deeply with the site (as
                            measured
                            by pageviews per session), and does this pattern differ by month? Knowing this would justify
                            <em>whether personalizing depth-of-engagement signals</em> is a viable path to higher
                            conversion.
                        </p>

                        <!-- 2. My Approach -->
                        <h3 class="sub-heading">My Approach</h3>
                        <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
                            <span class="badge bg-primary rounded-pill me-3 px-2 py-1">1</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Segment Definition:</strong> Defined <em>Purchasers</em> as users with
                                <code>totals.transactions >= 1</code> AND <code>productRevenue IS NOT NULL</code>.
                                <em>Non-Purchasers</em> were users with <code>transactions IS NULL</code> AND
                                <code>productRevenue IS NULL</code> — ensuring clean, mutually exclusive groups.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
                            <span class="badge bg-primary rounded-pill me-3 px-2 py-1">2</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Metric Design:</strong> Computed <strong>Average Pageviews per Unique
                                    Visitor</strong> (<code>SUM(pageviews) / COUNT(DISTINCT fullVisitorId)</code>) for
                                each
                                segment to normalize for different user counts.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
                            <span class="badge bg-primary rounded-pill me-3 px-2 py-1">3</span>
                            <div>
                                <strong>Safe Joining:</strong> Used a <code>FULL JOIN</code> (not INNER JOIN) between
                                the two CTEs to prevent data loss in months where one segment might have zero
                                representation.
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- 3. Solution -->
                        <h3 class="sub-heading">Solution</h3>
                        <div class="code-snippet-container shadow-sm">
                            <div class="code-header">
                                <span><i class="bi bi-code-slash me-2"></i>SQL Query</span>
                                <span class="badge bg-light text-dark border">BigQuery (GA Sessions 2017)</span>
                            </div>
                            <div id="sql-container-cs2"
                                style="max-height: 200px; overflow: hidden; transition: max-height 0.5s ease; position: relative;">
                                <pre class="mb-0"><code>WITH
  t6_t7_data AS(
    SELECT
      FORMAT_DATE('%Y%m',PARSE_DATE('%Y%m%d',date)) month,
      totals.transactions,
      product.productRevenue,
      totals.pageviews,
      fullVisitorId
    FROM `bigquery-public-data.google_analytics_sample.ga_sessions_2017*`,
      UNNEST(hits) hits,
      UNNEST(product) product
    WHERE _table_suffix BETWEEN '0601' AND '0731'
  ),

  purchase AS(
    SELECT
      month,
      ROUND(SUM(pageviews) / COUNT(DISTINCT fullVisitorId), 8) avg_pageviews_purchase
    FROM t6_t7_data
    WHERE transactions >= 1 AND productRevenue IS NOT NULL
    GROUP BY month
  ),

  non_purchase AS(
    SELECT
      month,
      ROUND(SUM(pageviews) / COUNT(DISTINCT fullVisitorId), 8) avg_pageviews_non_purchase
    FROM t6_t7_data
    WHERE transactions IS NULL AND productRevenue IS NULL
    GROUP BY month
    ORDER BY month
  )

SELECT *
FROM purchase
FULL JOIN non_purchase
USING(month)
ORDER BY month</code></pre>
                                <div id="sql-fade-cs2"
                                    style="position: absolute; bottom: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 80px; background: linear-gradient(transparent, #f8f9fa);">
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-center p-2 bg-light border-top">
                                <button id="btn-toggle-cs2"
                                    class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary fw-bold rounded-pill px-4"
                                    onclick="toggleSQL('cs2')">
                                    See More <i class="bi bi-chevron-down ms-1"></i>
                                </button>
